'''Noble Township''' is one of seven [[Civil township|townships]] in [[Wabash County, Indiana|Wabash County]], [[Indiana]], [[United States|USA]].  As of the [[United States Census, 2000|2000 census]], its population was 15,580.<ref>[http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/DTTable?_bm=y&-context=dt&-ds_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U&-mt_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U_P001&-CONTEXT=dt&-tree_id=4001&-all_geo_types=N&-geo_id=06000US1816954162&-search_results=01000US&-format=&-_lang=en United States Census Bureau American FactFinder]</ref>

==Geography==
According to the [[United States Census Bureau]], Noble Township covers an area of {{convert|82.56|sqmi}}; of this, {{convert|82.07|sqmi}} (99.41 percent) is land and {{convert|0.49|sqmi}} (0.59 percent) is water.

===Cities, towns, villages===
* [[Wabash, Indiana|Wabash]]

